reviews.headline: AMAZING PLUMPING GLOSS THAT ACTUALLY WORKS!
reviews.comments: The crappy reviews on this page are so frustrating!!!  The product is labeled EXTREME SENSATION for a reason....IT ACTUALLY WORKS!  So... if you can't stand the burn, don't buy the product and then leave a negative review.  Geez and duh!!!  That being said, this product is fabulous, comes in great color options and plumps like no other on the market.  LOVE IT!  Wimpy haters, be warned!

reviews.headline: Is this ghost pepper gloss?
reviews.comments: I was so excited to try this in a sample bundle I received. I put it on my bare lips and it tingled at first then 5 minutes went by and the burning set in. I washed it off and was left with little swollen bubble reaction on my lips. Unfortuntely had to throw it away. Proceed with caution.

reviews.headline: beautiful plumping lips
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Nyx Duck Plump High Pigment Plumping Lip Gloss suprises me on how it makes my lips look fuller without causing irritation. The color is very pretty and last long. Price is cheap but it is high quality.

reviews.headline: PLUMP TO THE MAX
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This gloss is NICE!!!!!!! The plumping effect is absolutely insane for this drugstore product!!! The packaging is nice and simple while the scent is equally pleasing!! Worth the money in my opinion!

reviews.headline: Great shine
reviews.comments: Great shine and color. Little spicy on the lips. But, overall good.

reviews.headline: Tingle, tingle, tingle
reviews.comments: This is a pretty tingly lipgloss. I have gotten it on my tongue and it kinda burns but it's not harmful. It has good coverage but doesn't last long then you have to reapply if you want.

reviews.headline: No Thank You
reviews.comments: It stung my lips and numbed my tongue. It taste nasty too.

reviews.headline: Does what it says, butâ€¦
reviews.comments: This is definitely effective. It gives your lips a plump look. It has good color payoff. The actually feeling and slip of the gloss feels nice, but it can get gloopy if you dont blot the inner portion of your lips. My problem with this product is purely personal preference and that is that the plumping agent in this is wayyyy too strong for my liking. I can handle the "extreme plump" lip injection from TF. But this was very uncomfortable to have on. And it has left my lips very chapped and dry. I unfortunately wont be using this again. But if you can handle the burning and the dry lips after, then go for it.

reviews.headline: Did not work for me
reviews.comments: It did absolutely nothing.

reviews.headline: OMG burn burn burn
reviews.comments: Did not read the comments before buying and trying. My lips, tongue and mouth are burning as I write this and I will be returning this to the store as fast as I can get there!

reviews.headline: Worth the burn!!

reviews.comments: I had to fill in a star, but it would be zero.  I had to was this off immediately.  It burns terrible.  IF it makes your lips fat, its because you are scrubbing it off your lips.  Terrible product.

reviews.headline: The Worst.
reviews.comments: I've used Buxom lip plumper for years.  I received a sample with an Ulta order and gave it a try.  This gloss is terrible.  It doesnt last, is super stingy and doesn't plump that well.  Complete junk.  I'll stick with my tried and true Buxom.

reviews.headline: BOMB
reviews.comments: This literally DELIVERS! my lips look so full and beautiful after using this and stays on throughout the day. Colors are beautiful and long lasting. Will definitely repurchase and highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Wanted to love this product!
reviews.comments: The color, quality and price are awesome! Maybe my lips are more sensitive, I don't know? It burned so bad I couldn't keep it on. The best thing I can compare it to would be Lip Injection, for those of you old enough to remember this plumper.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I didn't have high hopes for this because I'm honestly not usually a fan of NYX lip products. I love their eye and face stuff, and was stocking up during the sale, and needed to hit the free shipping minimum so I got this in Lilac on Loc. 

First, when I put it on, the applicator was pretty good. I was able to control where and how much of the product went on. That's good! Second, the tingle kicks in almost immediately, and be careful not to get any on your teeth or lick your lips because it will be spicy in your mouth in a not fun way â€” like burning. But I was surprised to see the plumping happen almost immediately. 

That said, I wasn't a fan of the shade on me and the thickness/opacity of it so after it sat a few minutes, I used a tissue to press my lips and that removed just the right amount. Then I lined my lips (with another brand that I love for lipliners, sorry) and I realized that I love this stuff! And it works! 

Now, I already have decently sized lips. But what this gave me was a puffier, "3D" volume that definitely stands out from a side view, and which I can also discern from the front. 

I think sometimes those who have thinner lips really hope for these lip plumpers to perform miracles but there's really only so much that they can do. If there's not a ton of lip material to start with, even if the product works great and plumps lips by say 15%, 15% of 5 is less than 15% of 10. See what I'm saying? 

Anyway, I really like this product and may buy it in other colors!
faceoff_positive.headline: Pleasantly surprised!
